cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) tasks in biomedical and clinical domains using a bi-directional long short-term memory network (BLSTM) and a linear conditional random field (CRF). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses neural architectures, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The use of BLSTM and CRF also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and analysis of errors, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible category.
